# WA template admin disable (strict)

When an admin hides a topic/template from surveys (power toggle in Admin → WA Templates):

- Set `active_for_survey=false` (survey) or `is_active=false` (feedback).
- Set `admin_hidden_from_survey=true` via `apply_admin_survey_visibility()` — **only** cleared when admin explicitly re-enables.

## Never auto re-enable

These paths must **not** flip hidden topics back on:

- MD seed / industry seed / test-pack seed
- Meta sync pull (`sync_from_meta`)
- `wa_template_unblock_repair_service`
- Clone/supersede cleanup scripts
- `ensure_system_templates` refresh

Use `may_auto_enable_for_survey(row)` before setting `active_for_survey=True` or `is_active=True`.

## Admin-only enable

Only admin endpoints with `_admin_visibility_override` may clear `admin_hidden_from_survey`:

- `POST /admin/wa-survey/templates/{id}/set-active`
- `POST /admin/customer-feedback/wa-templates` with `is_active`

## UI

Hidden rows: dimmed, sorted to bottom, label "Hidden from surveys". Optimistic update — no full reload on toggle.
